# Survey

## Summary

The `Survey` spec is a card definition that represents a survey, containing a title, description, and a list of survey questions.

## Import

```javascript
import { Survey } from '../survey';
```

## Usage as a Field

To use the `Survey` spec as a field within a consuming card or field, you can include it like this:

```typescript
import {
  CardDef,
  field,
  contains,
  containsMany,
} from 'https://cardstack.com/base/card-api';
import { Survey } from '../survey';

export class MyCard extends CardDef {
  @field survey = contains(Survey);
}
```

## Template Usage

To display a `Survey` within a template, you can use the following markup:

```handlebars
<div class="survey">
  <h2>{{this.survey.cardTitle}}</h2>
  <div class="survey-description">
    {{this.survey.description}}
  </div>
  {{#each this.survey.questions as |question|}}
    <div class="survey-question">
      {{question.text}}
    </div>
  {{/each}}
</div>
```
